uard with his left foot forward, both hands on the hilt of the sword, and with the blade pointing almost upwards, but maintaining a diagonal slant towards Dantess.  He was prepared for Dantess to make the first move, to gauge Visconti's speed and style.", "link_list": ["/user/1110"], "image_list": [], "html": "("}, "post-28617": {"user": "Dantess Visconti", "user_num": 1110, "timestamp": "1457989948000", "message": "\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0A gentle-natured chuckle and a genuine smile were all he was offered, as once Ralf took his stance Dantess himself stepped up to the challenge, positioning himself before his training student with his right side contorted forwards. While not completely profiled, his body presented a slimmer target, and his sword mirrored the spirit of his opponent's stance. The swept-hilt sword, glinting in the sun, was held forward with its tip facing diagonally up at Ralf's chin in the moderate grip of his right glove, an effective deterrent from several paces away.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0Yet when Dantess went to move, he didn't go right for Ralf--instead, he opted to begin walking in a casual circle that arced counter-clockwise around him.", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "<span>\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0</span>"}, "post-29103": {"user": "Ralf Valgard, the White Wolf", "user_num": 451, "timestamp": "1458256918000", "message": "(@dantess)Ralf watched Dantess with intense focus.  It was important that he present a suitable challenge to Dantess, even though Ralf himself was not exactly a well-trained fighter; Varan honor required it.Dantess mirrored Ralf's own movements, and began walking in a counter-clockwise circle.  He was waiting for Ralf to attack.  Ralf too walked counter-clockwise like Dantess, but only a few paces.  Ralf waited until the sun was shining in Dantess' eyes and then made his move.Ralf dashed forward to get into range.  He attacked with a light horizontal strike, aimed for the right side of Dantess' torso, just below